I attended Georgetown with Maya.  Roomed two doors down at Penberthy Hall.<br><br>
At dinner one night she picked up an artichoke and said that peeling away the leaves was like opening up people to new ways of thinking.  As one layer was exposed the old layer was used to nourish the spirit.<br><br>
The Wall is symbolic of that perspective on life.<br><br>
Maya if you see this tell Sam that Brenda still loves him!!<br><br>
Sam was Maya's dog &quot;Little Black Sambo&quot;<br><br>
Sure its not PC but Maya is no racist and the dog looks just like the illustrations in the Children's book before the fascists took them away.<br><br>
